filterProfile_FilterName.name: filterProfile_FilterName

filterProfile_OutputFilters_ValidEntry.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_ValidEntry
filterProfile_OutputFilters_ValidEntry.description: When TRUE, this filter entry has been defined and properly initialized. When FALSE, this entry should be skipped when filtering.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_Forward.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_Forward
filterProfile_OutputFilters_Forward.description: When TRUE a packet matching this filter will be forwarded or restart the idle timer. When FALSE a packet matching this filter will be dropped or not restart the idle timer.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_oType.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_oType
filterProfile_OutputFilters_oType.description: The type of filter contained in this entry. Used to select which of the following fields should be used.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Of.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Offset
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Of.description: Offset from start of frame of data to test.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Le.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Len
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Le.description: Number of octets to test. Max value is 8 octets.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Mo.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_More
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Mo.description: Include next entry in as part of filter.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Co.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_CompNeq
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Co.description: Defines type of comparison( Equals(FALSE) or Notequals(TRUE). Default is Equals.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Ma.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Mask
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Ma.description: A mask to be applied to the data at offset. Only the first len octets will be applied.

filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Va.name: filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Value
filterProfile_OutputFilters_GenFilter_Va.description: The value to compare with the masked data. Only the first len octets will be compared.
